						               													<description>Treasure Hunters is played on a board of seven spaces arranged in a ring. The players move around this - one clockwise and one counterclockwise - picking up four different values of treasure.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Movement is done by playing cards - one player has all the black cards from a standard deck and the other has the red, with random hands drawn from each. Most cards move the player around the board, but court cards have special effects.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player lands on a space they take the least-valuable treasure there, generally speaking. At the end of a turn a player may turn over one treasure on the board; treasures that have been turned over are worth more.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When all the treasures have been taken or all cards have been played the player with the most points in treasures wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
